com.enremmeta.rtb

Class LogUtils

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.enremmeta.rtb.LogUtils

  • public class LogUtils
extends Object

    Centralized place for logging calls (as static methods). Everything is logged at Level.INFO level unless otherwise specified.

    CONTRACT NOTE: This class is ONLY concerned with logging. The rationale is: we are only concerned about things that are to be analyzed later by an external actor. We are journalists/chroniclers, not participants in the action.

    We will only hold to the following conventions:
    • Columns are never removed from logging.

    The following things are true unless specified otherwise:

    • "Date" is always date/time more or less at the time of logging (which may be slightly later than actual event but not importantly so) formatted as LOG_DATE_FORMAT.
    • Unix time stamp is always, well, Unix time stamp more or less (because it's an asynchronous process) at the time of logging.
    • Both of the above are in UTC.
    • In structured logs, fields are tab-separated.
    • Campaign ID corresponds to ad ID.
    • Creative ID corresponds to tag ID.

    This is opinionated in a sense that:
    • Any null or empty field is logged as specified in DelimLayout).
    • We only recognize the following logs in the current implementation:
      • Structured (string TSV format suitable for loading into a DB; whenever lists of values are encountered in a field, they are written as CSV):
        • LOG_ACCESS - just the access URLs. See
        • LOG_BID - bids made ( logBid(OpenRtbRequest, long, String, String, String, Bid, int, int, ExchangeAdapter, String)
        • LOG_DEBUG_REQ debug companion to LOG_REQUEST
        • LOG_ABTEST_ASSIGNMENT - status assignment for A/B-test made for Campaign logExperimentCampaign(OpenRtbRequest, String, Ad, UserExperimentAttributes) or for Targeting Strategy logExperimentTargetingStrategy(OpenRtbRequest, String, Ad, UserExperimentAttributes)
        • LOG_REQUEST - all bid requests ( logRequest(OpenRtbRequest, boolean, int))
        • LOG_SESSION - same as LOG_REQUEST, but only for requests on which we bid.
        • URLs (see logRequest(OpenRtbRequest, boolean, int)).
        • LOG_WIN - wins (this is responsible for knowing the winning price). This may or may not be fired at the same time as #logImpression(String, String, String, String, String, String, long, String, String, String, String, String, HttpServletRequest, String, int, String, URI, String, String, String, String, String, MultivaluedMap, boolean, String, String, String, boolean, String) in cases where an exchange requires using NUrl mechanism ( BRX is one such example). See logWin(String, String, String, String, String, String, String, double, long, long, long, String, String, String, String, String, HttpServletRequest, String, Long, String, URI, boolean, String, String, String, String, String, String, boolean, boolean, String)
        • LOG_PSEUDOWIN - pseudo-wins -- same as above but where authoritativeWin is false
        • LOG_IMPRESSION - impressions. See #logImpression(String, String, String, String, String, String, long, String, String, String, String, String, HttpServletRequest, String, int, String, URI, String, String, String, String, String, MultivaluedMap, boolean, String, String, String, boolean, String)
        • LOG_CLICK - clicks. See logClick(String, String, String, String, String, String, String, String, String, String, HttpServletRequest, String, String, URI, String, String, String, String)
        • LOG_LOST- lost bids. See logLost(Long, String, String, String, String, Long, Long, String, String, String, String, HttpServletRequest, String, String, String, String)
      • Semi-structured:
        • LOG_RESPONSE - entire bid response ( logResponse(OpenRtbRequest, OpenRtbResponse, Object))
        • LOG_RAW_REQUEST - raw request as JSON. ( logRawRequest(OpenRtbRequest, Object, UriInfo))
      • Unstructured:
        • LOG_MAIN - free-form logging for troubleshooting. See:
          • trace(Object)
          • debug(Object)
          • info(Object)
          • error(Object)
          • error(Object, Throwable)

      • logBid

        public static void logBid(OpenRtbRequest req,
                          long timeSpent,
                          String bidRequestId,
                          String userId,
                          String modUid,
                          Bid bid,
                          int candCount,
                          int bidCount,
                          ExchangeAdapter adapter,
                          String outcome)
        Log a bid. Will log the following information, in order, to LOG_BID.
        1. Current date (assume UTC)
        2. Current time stamp
        3. Time spent to get this bid
        4. bid request ID
        5. Our User ID
        6. bid ID
        7. impression ID
        8. campaign ID - we define this to be targeting ID
        9. creative ID - we define this to be tag ID
        10. Bid, as $ CPM
        11. Bid, as micro-$ per impression.
        12. M1 literal
        13. M2 literal
        14. Count of bid candidates considered by BidCandidateManager.
        15. Count of bids returned for this bid request.
        16. Exchange
        17. bid choice algo
        18. SSP
        19. "M3" literal
        20. How many bids left to make in this period
        21. How many bids we were originally supposed to make in this period
        22. node ID
        23. seqBid sequential number of bid per node (see above)
        24. Mod UID
        25. Ad.getAdVersion() version of the Ad
        26. Tag.getTagVersion() version of the Tag
        27. Outcome - one of Lot49Constants.BID_OUTCOME_SUBMITTED, @link Lot49Constants.BID_OUTCOME_INTERNAL_AUCTION_LOSS, @link Lot49Constants.BID_OUTCOME_CONTROL.
        Parameters:
        userId - User.getBuyeruid()
        See Also:
        Utils.microToCpm(double), Utils.cpmToMicro(double)

      • logExperimentCampaign

        public static void logExperimentCampaign(OpenRtbRequest req,
                                         String modUid,
                                         Ad ad,
                                         UserExperimentAttributes exptAttributes)
        Log an A/B-test assignment on Campaign. Will log the following information, in order, to LOG_ABTEST_ASSIGNMENT.
        1. Current date (assume UTC)
        2. Current time stamp
        3. bid request ID
        4. Our User ID
        5. Cookie as decoded by Utils.cookieToLogModUid(String)
        6. C literal - experiment assignment on Campaign
        7. Campaign id
        8. Campaign A/B-test status ("T", "C" or "N")
        9. Version of A/B-test.
        10. Full User A/B-test status
        11. User segments as a comma-separated list each encrypted with an advertiser's key.
        12. Campaign id
        13. (region )
        Parameters:

      • logRequest

        public static void logRequest(OpenRtbRequest req,
                              boolean didBid,
                              int candidates)

        Log every Impression request (could be multiple per actual bid request). Note that not all fields are logged at all levels. Check the documentation per field. When not otherwise specified, everything here applies to INFO level.

        This actually writes more than one log:
        • In case of didBid being false, entries to three logs are written:
          1. request log which has hashed URLs (per standard business agreements with publishers and exchanges that this information cannot be shared with third parties)
          2. URL log where actual URLs and their hashes are stored which can be referred to hashed URLs from the above one (per standard business agreements with publishers and exchanges that this information cannot be shared with third parties)
          3. debug request log which has extra information useful for debugging.
        • If didBid is true (this happens when we decide to bid, and happens after the above, but much less frequently), a copy of the entry written earlier to LOG_REQUEST is now written to LOG_SESSION. The other files are not written at this point.

        Request log

        The following fields are logged, in this order (remember that any null or empty field is logged as DelimLayout.getNullChar()).

        1. Current date in human-readable format. We are always assuming this to be in UTC.
        2. Unix epoch time. We are always assuming this to be in UTC.
        3. M0, as a literal.
        4. Exchange (e.g., openx).
        5. Bid request ID
        6. Impression ID
        7. Our cookie, after corrections. See below for original version.
        8. Exchange's user ID
        9. Custom data we synced with Exchange on user
        10. User segments, encrypted with Lot49Config.getLogKey(), or plain text if that is null or empty.
        11. city based on Device.getGeo()
        12. region/state/province based on Device.getGeo()
        13. zip/postal code based on Device.getGeo()
        14. latitude based on Device.getGeo()
        15. longitude based on Device.getGeo()
        16. metro code based on Device.getGeo()
        17. city based on user
        18. region/state/province based on user
        19. zip/postal code based on user
        20. latitude based on user
        21. longitude based on user
        22. metro code based on user
        23. city based on our own lookup
        24. region/state/province based on our own lookup
        25. zip/postal code based on our own lookup
        26. latitude based on our own lookup
        27. longitude based on our own lookup
        28. metro code based on our own lookup
        29. Gender (per Exchange's opinion)
        30. IP address of the user
        31. User-agent of the user's browser
        32. M1 literal (marker)
        33. Make of user's device
        34. Model of user's device
        35. OS of user's device
        36. OS version of user's device
        37. Language of a user's device
        38. MD5 hash of the domain Domain
        39. Categories for site
        40. Keywords for site
        41. Name
        42. MD5-hashed Page URL
        43. Page category
        44. Content categories
        45. Content keywords
        46. Content language
        47. Type ("video" or "banner")
        48. Size (width x height)
        49. Mimes (Banner.getMimes() or Video.getMimes())
        50. Video.getApi() or Banner.getApi()
        51. linearity
        52. protocols
        53. min duration
        54. max duration
        55. X-Forwarded-For header value
        56. Country from Device
        57. Country from User
        58. Country looked up by us
        59. Section categories
        60. timezone
        61. user's domain
        62. user's ISP
        63. organization
        64. connection type
        65. test?
        66. Literal "X1"
        67. Literal marker "M2".
        68. User-data stored at Exchange and passed to us.
        69. Lot49CustomData.getUid()
        70. @param candidates -- how many candidates in BidCandidateManager, that is, how many ads we are considering eligible for this request, pending data request.
        71. Literal "M3".
        72. Lot49Ext.getRealIpHeader()
        73. Lot49Ext.getRemoteHost()
        74. Lot49Ext.getRemotePort()
        75. Lot49Ext.getRemoteAddr()
        76. ext object as is
        77. Literal "M4".
        78. Device type (see section 6.16 of OpenRTB spec.)
        79. User's Unix timestamp
        80. User's day of week
        81. Bidder's day of week
        82. User's hour
        83. Bidder's hour
        84. User's timestamp as string
        85. Literal "M5"
        86. SSP (actual exchange if the request is from an aggregator, or same as exchange).
        87. forceCookieReset
        88. forceCookieResync
        89. receivedBuyerUid
        90. Literal "X2"
        91. Literal "M6"
        92. Integral Ad Science's data
        93. bid choice algo
        94. browser name
        95. browser family
        96. third party provider information
        97. skyhook categories
        98. "M7" as a literal
        99. whether SSL was required
        100. excluded markups, as a list (see MarkupType ).
        101. Bid floor
        102. mod_uid encoding of cookie.
        103. "M8" as a literal
        104. other region names
        105. Private deals info
        106. node ID
        107. region of the node
        108. User segments as a comma-separated list each encrypted with an advertiser's key.
        109. "M9" as a literal
        110. App name
        111. App bundle ID

        URL log

        LOG_URLS is written with the following fields:
        1. Current date in human-readable format. We are always assuming this to be in UTC.
        2. Unix epoch time. We are always assuming this to be in UTC.
        3. Server ID
        4. Exchange
        5. Bid request ID
        6. Impression ID
        7. URL
        8. MD5 hash of the URL
        9. SSP (actual exchange if the request is from an aggregator, or same as exchange).
        10. Our cookie
        11. Exchange's user ID
        12. Custom data we synced with Exchange on user
        13. mod_uid encoding of cookie.
        14. Domain
        15. MD5 hash of the Domain

        Debug request log

        LOG_DEBUG_REQ is written with following fields:
        1. Current date in human-readable format. We are always assuming this to be in UTC.
        2. Unix epoch time. We are always assuming this to be in UTC.
        3. Bid request ID
        4. Impression ID
        5. optout reasons
        6. Literal "M1"
        7. comments
        8. Literal "M2"
